---
import Configurator from "../../components/Configurator.astro";
import DocCode from "../../components/DocCode.astro";
import DocsCallout from "../../components/DocsCallout.astro";
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
import PlatformCodeBlock from "../../components/PlatformCodeBlock.astro";
import { Code } from 'astro:components';
import { SHIKI_THEMES } from '../../lib/shiki-config.js';
import { getChunkhoundVersion } from "../../lib/version";

const chunkhoundVersion = getChunkhoundVersion();
const posixCode = `# Skip if you already have uv\ncurl -LsSf https://astral.sh/uv/install.sh | sh\nuv tool install chunkhound`;
const psCode = `# Skip if you already have uv\npowershell -ExecutionPolicy ByPass -c "irm https://astral.sh/uv/install.ps1 | iex"\nuv tool install chunkhound`;
---

<DocsLayout
    title="Getting Started"
    description="Install ChunkHound, pick your stack, index your code, and verify search end to end."
>
    <h1>Get ChunkHound running<span class="title-dot" aria-hidden="true"
        ></span></h1>
    <p class="lead">
        Install the CLI, pick your stack, index your code. Three commands, two
        minutes.
    </p>

    <h2>Install</h2>
    <PlatformCodeBlock dataCopy={posixCode}>
        <div data-platform-code="posix" data-platform-copy={posixCode}>
            <Code lang="bash" themes={SHIKI_THEMES} defaultColor={false} code={posixCode} />
        </div>
        <div data-platform-code="powershell" hidden data-platform-copy={psCode}>
            <Code lang="powershell" themes={SHIKI_THEMES} defaultColor={false} code={psCode} />
        </div>
    </PlatformCodeBlock>
    <p>Verify the install resolved on your shell:</p>
    <DocCode code="chunkhound --version" />
    <DocsCallout title="Expected output" variant="success">
        <pre><code>chunkhound {chunkhoundVersion}</code></pre>
        <p>
            A version line on stdout. If you see <code>command not found</code>,
            fix your shell <code>PATH</code> before continuing.
        </p>
    </DocsCallout>

    <p class="picker-lead">
        Choose your editor, embedding provider, and LLM. Copy the three commands
        below and run them from your project root.
    </p>
    <p>
        For local or proxied OpenAI-compatible LLM backends like Ollama or
        vLLM, keep the generated <code>llm.model</code> value in place.
        ChunkHound requires an explicit model name for custom
        <code>base_url</code> endpoints, including per-role overrides that
        resolve to OpenAI-compatible providers.
    </p>
    <Configurator heading="Pick your stack" compact={false} />

    <h2>Index and verify</h2>
    <p>
        Run these four commands in order. Each one verifies a different layer of
        the stack: database, regex search, embeddings, then LLM.
    </p>

    <h4>1. Index the project</h4>
    <DocCode code="chunkhound index ." />
    <DocsCallout title="Expected output" variant="success">
        <pre><code>Indexed 412 files, 6,841 chunks
Database: .chunkhound/db/chunks.db</code></pre>
        <p>
            File and chunk counts will differ; the <code>Indexed</code> prefix and
            the <code>.chunkhound/db/chunks.db</code> path are stable.
        </p>
    </DocsCallout>

    <h4>2. Confirm regex search</h4>
    <DocCode code={`chunkhound search --regex "import"`} />
    <DocsCallout title="Expected output" variant="success">
        <pre><code>Found 1,284 matches
src/main.py:1: import os</code></pre>
        <p>
            A match count and at least one truncated result line. Zero matches with
            no error usually means the <code>--db</code> path is wrong &mdash; see
            <a href="/docs/configuration/">Configuration</a> for the canonical
            database path rules.
        </p>
    </DocsCallout>

    <h4>3. Confirm semantic search</h4>
    <DocCode code={`chunkhound search "authentication flow"`} />
    <DocsCallout title="Expected output" variant="success">
        <pre><code>score   file:line                          snippet
0.81    src/auth/session.py:42             def login(...)
0.74    src/auth/middleware.py:18          class AuthMiddleware</code></pre>
        <p>
            A ranked list with a score column. If regex worked but this didn't,
            your embedding provider credentials are missing or wrong.
        </p>
    </DocsCallout>

    <h4>4. Confirm research</h4>
    <DocCode code={`chunkhound research "How does authentication work?"`} />
    <DocsCallout title="Expected output" variant="success">
        <pre><code>Authentication is handled by src/auth/session.py, which...</code></pre>
        <p>
            A short natural-language answer that cites real files. If search
            worked but this didn't, your LLM provider credentials are missing or
            wrong, or the LLM CLI you picked isn't on <code>PATH</code>.
        </p>
    </DocsCallout>

    <h2>Use it from your agent</h2>
    <p>
        Your agent already has ChunkHound &mdash; the editor command from
        <strong>Pick your stack</strong> registered it as an MCP tool. The
        biggest unlock is calling <code>code_research</code> <em>before</em>
        writing code, not after.
    </p>
    <p>
        <code>code_research</code> synthesises a cited markdown report covering
        architecture, key locations, and cross-file flows. One call usually
        replaces 5&ndash;10 manual searches.
    </p>

    <h3>Example prompts</h3>
    <p>The pattern is one line. Paste it into your editor chat with a topic of your own:</p>
    <DocCode lang="text" code="Use chunkhound research to ..." />
    <p>A few directions to start with:</p>
    <ul class="prompt-ideas">
        <li>explain how authentication works end to end, with file:line citations</li>
        <li>map every caller of the email subsystem and the helpers they share</li>
        <li>trace the login flow from form submit to Set-Cookie</li>
        <li>find every file-upload handler and compare their size limits, MIME validation, and storage targets</li>
        <li>diagnose duplicate webhook deliveries by tracing the handler outward through retries, queues, and idempotency keys</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
        Need just a file or symbol? Ask the agent to use <code>chunkhound search</code>
        instead &mdash; it's faster and skips the LLM.
    </p>

    <h3 id="mcp">MCP integration</h3>
    <p>
        ChunkHound exposes <code>code_research</code>, <code>search</code>, and
        a handful of other tools as an <abbr title="Model Context Protocol"
            >MCP</abbr
        > server; your editor connected to it via the command in
        <strong>Pick your stack</strong>.
    </p>

    <h2>Where to next</h2>
    <div class="next-grid">
        <a href="/docs/configuration/" class="next-card">
            <h4>Configuration</h4>
            <p>
                Full config shape, provider details, indexing controls, and
                environment-variable overrides.
            </p>
        </a>
        <a href="/docs/cli-reference/" class="next-card">
            <h4>CLI Reference</h4>
            <p>
                Every command, every flag, and the syntax for advanced indexing
                and research workflows.
            </p>
        </a>
    </div>
    <p class="exit">
        Stuck? Ask in <a href="https://discord.gg/BAepHEXXnX">Discord</a> or
        <a href="https://github.com/chunkhound/chunkhound/issues">open an issue</a>.
    </p>
</DocsLayout>

<style>
    .title-dot {
        display: inline-block;
        width: 0.18em;
        height: 0.18em;
        border-radius: 50%;
        background: var(--primary-bright);
        margin-left: 0.05em;
        vertical-align: baseline;
    }

    .lead {
        margin-bottom: var(--space-7);
        font-size: var(--text-lg);
        line-height: var(--lh-lg);
        color: var(--text-secondary);
    }

    /* The picker lead sits above the Configurator's own centered heading,
       so it acts as the §2 section intro. Push it down to space it from
       the previous section before the Configurator's own padding kicks in. */
    .picker-lead {
        margin-top: var(--space-8);
    }

    /* Tighten the success callouts so the inner pre/p stack reads as one
       confirmation block, not two stacked surfaces. */
    :global(.docs-callout-success) :global(pre) {
        margin-top: 0;
        margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
        background: transparent;
        padding: 0;
    }

    :global(.docs-callout-success) :global(pre code) {
        font-size: var(--text-sm);
        color: var(--text-primary);
    }

    .next-grid {
        display: grid;
        gap: var(--space-5);
        grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
        margin-top: var(--space-5);
    }

    .next-card {
        display: block;
        padding: var(--space-5);
        border: var(--border-w-default) solid var(--border-subtle);
        border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
        background: var(--bg-surface);
        color: inherit;
        text-decoration: none;
        transition:
            border-color 0.2s,
            background 0.2s;
    }

    :global(html[data-theme="light"]) .next-card {
        border-color: var(--border-color);
    }

    .next-card:hover {
        border-color: var(--primary);
        text-decoration: none;
    }

    .next-card h4 {
        margin-top: 0;
        margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
    }

    .exit {
        margin-top: var(--space-5);
        color: var(--text-secondary);
    }

    @media (max-width: 640px) {
        .next-grid {
            grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        }
    }
</style>
